of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuzonN","text_ar":"حُزْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dilatation of the bosom with delight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasure, wherein is quiet"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tranquillity"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rest of mind, of short"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of long continuance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whereas"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraHN","text_ar":"فَرَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is dilatation of the bosom with delight, or pleasure, of short continuance, transitory, or fleeting, not lasting, as is the case in bodily and worldly pleasures; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraH","text_ar":"فَرَح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suruwr","text_ar":"سُرُور"},{"kind":"text","text":", and vice versâ: (Er-Rághib, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frH","text_ar":"فرح"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suruwrN","text_ar":"سُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delight, and dilatation of the heart, of which there is no external sign;"},{"kind":"text","text":"distinguished from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is cheerfulness, i. e., pleasure, or delight, or dilatation of the heart, which has a visible effect in the aspect. (TA.)       -A2-  Also sing. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sururN","text_ar":"سُرُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) which signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper extremities of the stems"},{"kind":"text","text":"of plants. (K, TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masar~apN","text_ar":"مَسَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Msb","IAar","Sgh","K","TA"]}]}}